  <h2>📅 04/07/25</h2>

  <div class="news-item">
    <h2>🔥 Vulnerabilities</h2>
    <p>Grafana patched four Chromium-based RCE vulnerabilities in Image Renderer and Synthetic Monitoring Agent. Self-hosted users must upgrade. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/grafana-releases-critical-security-update-for-image-renderer-plugin/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>Cisco resolved CVE-2025-20309—hardcoded root credentials in Unified CM enabling remote RCE. <a href="https://www.helpnetsecurity.com/2025/07/03/cisco-fixes-maximum-severity-flaw-in-enterprise-unified-comms-platform-cve-2025-20309/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>Apache patched Tomcat (CVE-2025-24813) and Camel (CVE-2025-27636, -29891) vulnerabilities, following rapid proof-of-concept releases and global exploitation. <a href="https://unit42.paloaltonetworks.com/apache-cve-2025-24813-cve-2025-27636-cve-2025-29891/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
  </div>

  <div class="news-item">
    <h2>🕵️ Adversaries & Attacks</h2>
    <p>BlueNoroff group uses fake Zoom SDK scripts and AppleScript droppers to target crypto and gambling firms. <a href="https://www.cysecurity.news/2025/07/north-korean-hackers-target-fintech-and.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>Chinese actors spoof Apple, Michael Kors, and more with fake shopping sites to steal payment data. <a href="https://hackread.com/china-fake-marketplace-mimics-top-retail-brands-fraud/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>40+ fake Firefox extensions impersonating wallets like MetaMask and Trust Wallet to steal credentials. <a href="https://thehackernews.com/2025/07/over-40-malicious-firefox-extensions.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
    <p>Attackers inject trojans in ConnectWise installers via Authenticode certificate stuffing, evading signature checks. <a href="https://www.cysecurity.news/2025/07/hackers-exploit-connectwise.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
